<HEADLINE> Cambodian Assembly Adopts 1998 Budget </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The National Assembly of
Cambodia Wednesday adopted the 1998 budget, with defence spending
being the top priority.
</P>
<P>
The budget, totalling 1,445 billion riel (about 419 billion
U.S. dollars), is about five percent lower that of this year due
to the decrease of international aid.
</P>
<P>
Defense spending, which is about 20 percent of the budget, is
followed by domestic and educational spendings. 
</P>
