<HEADLINE> Salim Calls for Stepping up Economic Recovery in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Salim Ahmed Salim,
secretary general of the Organization of African Unity (OAU),
today appealed to Africans to accelerate economic recovery and
development in their continent.
</P>
<P>
In his new year message issued here, Salim said: "One of the
ways of building peace in our continent is through the
acceleration of Africa's economic recovery and development and
full integration into the global economy."
</P>
<P>
Salim stressed that Africa must no longer be left behind in
the global attempt to promote trade and investment.
</P>
<P>
He said that the inaugural summit of the African Economic
Community held in Harare last June signaled the determination by
Africa to take its destiny in its own hands and assume greater
responsibility for the economic development of the continent.
</P>
<P>
Salim hoped that Africans will work for the integration of
their respective economies to pull together to boost trade and
their economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He appealed to all those in leadership positions, especially
in those societies where innocent young men, women and the
elderly have been traumatized by the scourge of war and conflict,
"to take advantage of the blessings that come with the new year
to observe a truce, cease all hostilities and allow the efforts
towards peace and reconciliation to yield the required
dividends".
</P>
<P>
Salim stressed that the struggle for peace, security and
stability of our continent is " the responsibility of each and
every one of us whatever his or her position is and wherever he
or she is". 
</P>
</TEXT>
