<HEADLINE> Mozambique to Launch First Free Industrial Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican Prime Minister
Pascoal Mocumbi announced here today that the country will set up
its first free industrial zone (ZFI) in Maputo Province in
1998.
</P>
<P>
Mocumbi said at a press conference that an Aluminum plant using
imported raw materials will be built in the ZFI,
which will be located in Beloluane, Boane County,
</P>
<P>
The Aluminum plant will cost about 1.2 billion U.S. dollars
and is expected to be operational by the end of 1999, the prime
minister said, adding that it will be able to create over 4,000
jobs.
</P>
<P>
Mocumbi expressed the hope that the planned free indurstrial zone
will give a boost to the development of industries and the whole
economy of Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
The ZFI will give a "positive signal" to all the
foreign investors in Mozambique, he said, adding that the
government will try its best to actualize the plan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
