<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano, in a new year message today, called on his people to
make their own contributions to ensure success of the country's
1998 social and economic plan.
</P>
<P>
In the message, he said the government will step up the
control of inflation, reduce the economy's dependence on external
donors and promote efficiency and modernization of the banking
sector in the coming new year.
</P>
