<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Women MPs Call for Respect for Women's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian women
parliament members today called for the practical application of
women's rights enshrined in the constitution.
</P>
<P>
In a declaration issued at the end of a five-day Women
Parliament Members Forum held in Ardaita of Oromo region, the
participants said the present laws which are related to women or
in contravention to the constitution should be nullified and
replaced by other laws in line with the constitution for the
respect for women's rights.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from the Ethiopian News Agency, the
participants said they will strive to ensure women's rights of
property ownership and management in their respective regions
until new laws are promulgated.
</P>
<P>
They asked for amendments on women's pension and maternity
leave rights which are currently applicable in the statutes of
social security authority and civil service commission
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The organization of women is indispensable to ensure
constitutional rights and fight gender repression, they said, and
vowed to exert unstinting joint efforts to prevent crimes on
women which lead to physical and psychological damages.
</P>
<P>
The participants also urged the women's affairs sector of the
prime minister's office and the women's affairs committee of the
House of People's Representatives to investigate and resolve
impediments in materializing policies in this regard. 
</P>
