<HEADLINE> Air Passenger Traffic Continues to Fall in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The number of air passengers in
Nigeria's 20 airports dropped from 2.3 million last year to 1.73
million this year, the Federal Airport Authority of Nigeria
(FAAN) said today.
</P>
<P>
According to a FAAN report, the fall follows the pattern of
passenger traffic in the country since 1983 when a total of 6.05
million passengers travelled by air.
</P>
<P>
It shows that 5.19 million passengers used the airports in
1982 while in 1984 passenger traffic was 5.98 million.
</P>
<P>
The report said that in 1987 and 1988, 5.79 million and 3.95
million passengers were recorded respectively, while in 1990 the
figure dropped to 3.76 million.
</P>
<P>
A total of 5.06 million passengers used the facilities in
1991, and the number of air passengers increased to 5.47 million
and 5.51 million in 1992 and 1993 respectively, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The figure was down to 4.54 million in 1994 and went up
slightly to 4.86 million, the News Agency of Nigeria quoted the
report as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
