<HEADLINE> Iraq Again Condemns Turkish Troop Invasion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Baghdad, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Iraq again expressed its
strong condemnation today of Turkish troop invasion of its
territory and called for its immediate withdrawal from northern
Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The denouncement was uttered by a Foreign Ministry spokesman in
response to Turkey's announced termination of the latest Turkish
cross-border military operation in northern Iraq Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the announced termination of Turkish
military operation in northern Iraq which began December 25 was in
fact a recurrence of what Turkey used to say in the wake of its
continuing invasions.
</P>
<P>
Turkish troops have been engaged in frequent operations in
northern Iraq to wipe out the militants of its outlawed Kurdish
Workers' Party since 1995 when Baghdad lost effective control over
the area.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi spokesman said that once again Turkey used this ploy
to justify its practices, namely, the pursuit of rebel elements
hostile to the Turkish government.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out such statements were nothing but attempts to
mislead the Turkish public opinion, and to contain worldwide
condemnation of Turkey's aggressive policies. 
</P>
