<HEADLINE> Ramadan Begins in Algeria with Massacre of 78 Civilians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Seventy-eight civilians were
massacred from Tuesday night till this morning in western Algeria
by Islamic militants, on the eve of the Muslim fasting month of
Ramadan which began today, according to reports from Algeria
quoting Algerian security force.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-one people were killed and 20 injured in one attack by
an armed group in the village of Ouled Kherarba in the Relizane
region in western Algeria.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-nine other villagers were killed and 21 injured in
another attack upon the village of Ouled Selma, while 28 more were
killed and 27 injured in a village called Ouled Taieb, all in the
same region.
</P>
<P>
The latest massacre brought the official figure of people
killed over the past 10 days to 428.
</P>
<P>
The Algerian government has appealed to people to be vigilant
during the Ramadan, a month considered to be a period for waging
the "jihad," or holy war, by Islamic militants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
