<HEADLINE> Iranian Political Party Announces Its Formation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 31 (Xinhua) -- A party named Iranian People's
Freedom Party today declared its existence, a challenging
political move to the Islamic rule which has been banning any
political parties in the country for years.
</P>
<P>
The party announced in a statement that its main objectives
were to safeguard freedom of expression, individual and social
security, equal social rights, to eliminate racial, religious,
cultural, language discriminations, to create peaceful atmosphere
for all Iranian tribes.
</P>
<P>
The party would also make efforts to reform the country's
economic structure and look into the needs of the young generation
and the legal demands of millions of Iranians living abroad.
</P>
<P>
The statement noted that the Iranian People's Freedom Party was
demanding legal approval from the authorities, adding that after
being approved, it would make public its detailed goals and
objectives.
</P>
<P>
The party expressed regret for the absence of political parties
in Iran, because of which the traditional religious groups had
played an active role in Iran's politics, according to the
statement.
</P>
<P>
The party called for the establishment of political parties
with clear objectives under the situations after Khatami came to
power last August.
</P>
<P>
Since Khatami was elected Iran's president, moderate Iranians,
including intellectuals, women, young people, began to consider
forming their own political parties.
</P>
<P>
Last month, Faezeh Hashemi, daughter of former Iranian
president and incumbent Chairman of the powerful Expediency
Council Hashemi Rafsanjani, announced that the moderate Group-6
have decided to form a political party in the near future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
