<HEADLINE> Romania Enlarges Benefits for Foreign Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, January 1 (Xinhua) -- In an effort to attract more
foreign investment, Romania has issued new laws to enlarge the
benefits of foreign investors effective for five years from
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Under the new laws, foreigners could invest in any economic
sector of Romania just as the Romanian citizens do. And regardless
of their nationality and residence, they will also be entitled to
benefits on taxes.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, Romania attracted a record 1.5 billion U.S. dollars in
foreign investment, but still lags behind other Central and
Eastern European countries, such as Poland, Hungary and the Czech
Republic. 
