<HEADLINE> Sino-Russian Chemical Project Successful in Test Run </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, January 1 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-Russian chemical
industrial project to produce polytetrafluoroethylene recently
went into test operations in east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The Zhejiang Juhua Corporation Group and a national research
center of applied chemistry of Russia cooperated in the project,
said to be the biggest Sino-Russian joint venture in China.
</P>
