<HEADLINE> Poor Workers Receive New Year's Greetings, Gifts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Throughout the country, central
and local Communist Party and governmental officials have been
active around the New Year showing compassion for laid-off workers
and others in need.
</P>
<P>
In northeast China, Liaoning Governor Wen Shizhen and other
officials braved biting cold on Wednesday and Thursday to visit
financially troubled state-run factories and poor workers, calling
on the staff members to work hard to solve the difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Led by Liaoning Provincial Federation of Trade Unions Chairman
Li Shixue, a delegation visited troubled enterprises and homes of
poor workers in the last two days of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Before the New Year, the Liaoning provincial government had
dispatched nine delegations to convey solicitude for those in
financial difficulty across the province.
</P>
<P>
In Harbin, capital of northeast China's Heilongjiang Province,
more than 20,000 Party and government officials went to the homes
of poor workers to deliver money, flour, meat and vegetable for
the New Year.
</P>
<P>
In southwest China's Chongqing Municipality, the city
government has been emphasizing the relocation of laid-off
workers. This morning, dozens of previously laid-off workers went
to the city's re-employment training center to write New Year's
couplets as a way to express their gratitude.
</P>
<P>
Pu Haiqing, mayor of Chongqing, also sent flour, rice and money
to poor retired workers. Local sources said that the city has set
up a special 10-million-yuan fund for poor workers.
</P>
<P>
Around the New Year, officials with the All-China Federation of
Trade Unions (ACFTU) also went to different places throughout the
country to extend New Year's greetings.
</P>
<P>
ACFTU Vice-chairman Zhang Dinghua went to Zhengzhou City in
central China's Henan Province to visit workers' homes. Ni Haomei,
another ACFTU vice-chairman, went to Yan'an City in northwest
China's Shaanxi Province conveying New Year's greetings and
presenting gifts.
</P>
<P>
Likewise, local officials in areas such as Nanjing City,
Shandong Province, Guizhou Province, and Kunming City have visited
businesses in difficulty and homes of poor workers, extending
solicitudes on behalf of the Party and government departments and
providing food and other daily necessities for the New Year.
</P>
