<HEADLINE> Wong Takes Overall Title at South China Sea Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's top cyclist Wong
Kam-po took the overall title of the South China Sea Cycling Race
which was concluded here Thursday after the sixth and last race
competition.
</P>
<P>
Despite losing out in the final tour, which was won by Xie
Guofang, Chinese Taipei, Wong retained his title with an overall
time of 10 hours 27 minutes and 18 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Xie, from Kaohsiung Team, wrapped up the 40 laps, 66-kilometer
Macao tour in a time of one hour 28 minutes and 51 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Wong, Hong Kong's first ever Chinese National Games gold
medalist, won the first two stages held in Hong Kong en rout to
the comprehensive triumph of the six-day, 426-kilometer race which
featured three tours of Hong Kong, Zhuhai and Macao.
</P>
<P>
The team title went to Japan and the individual points crown
belonged to the Chen Genxian of Chinese Taipei. 
</P>
