<HEADLINE> Leading Chinese Bank Backs Commercial Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial
Bank of China (ICBC), one of the nation's four biggest state-owned
commercial banks, increased its loan support to businesses in 1997.
</P>
<P>
A total of 39.64 billion yuan of loans were granted to nearly
7,000 commercial companies by the first quarter of December,
either through loan extensions or bills accepted, according to
statistics from the ICBC branches in 30 cities.
</P>
<P>
The bank has also focused its loan support on those
best-performers whose economic efficiency and high credit ratings
guarantee low repayment risks.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that loans to the 299 large-size shopping malls
and chain store groups were nearly 5 billion yuan by Dec. 10, up
20 percent over the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Aside from extending loans, the bank also helped ease the cash
shortage of the commercial sector, with 1.25 billion yuan in bills
accepted for the first quarter of December alone. 
</P>
