<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Media Confident in Future of China, SAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Some major Hong Kong
newspapers on Thursday published New Year's Day editorials and
commentaries, expressing their confidence in the future of China
and of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
Looking back at the past year, Ta Kung Pao said in a commentary
that 1997 was a year full of changes in the history of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, Hong Kong returned to the motherland smoothly, the SAR
government had a good beginning of its work, the chief executive
and the SAR government were trusted by the central government,
supported by the Hong Kong people and praised by foreigners, the
commentary said.
</P>
<P>
The commentary noted that the six million Hong Kong people will
not be defeated by temporary difficulties such as the Asian
financial turmoil and the "bird flu".
</P>
<P>
It pointed out that in 1998, the Hong Kong people will face new
tests which are by no means less difficult than those in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The legislative election to be held in May is another
demonstration of the further implementation of the policy of "one
country, two systems" and "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong",
the commentary said.
</P>
<P>
The Wen Wei Po said in an editorial that the Chinese people
experienced a great sorrow in early 1997 when Deng Xiaoping, the
chief designer of the reform and opening up of China, passed away.
</P>
<P>
The past year was also a happy year for the Chinese people, the
editorial said. The Chinese government not only resumed its
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong but also successfully kept
its prosperity and stability, the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, China achieved a nine-percent economic growth, a
record of 135 billion U.S. dollars of foreign exchange reserves
and a 20 percent exports expansion, the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
The country's economic development will give strong support to
the economic development of the Hong Kong SAR, the editorial
pointed out. Hong Kong will have a better future, it added.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Commercial Daily said in a commentary that the
15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) held
in September 1997 has drafted a guideline of action for the
transcentury development of the country.
</P>
<P>
In the new year, China will continue to carry out the policy of
reform and will be further opened up and the country's economy
will keep growing, the commentary said.
</P>
<P>
The fast economic development of the country offers a good
environment for the economic development of the SAR, it noted.
</P>
<P>
Under the policy of "one country, two systems", the roads
leading to the 21st century for China and its Hong Kong SAR will
become broader and broader, the commentary said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
