<HEADLINE> Most Italians Optimistic About 1998, Except for Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Most Italians foresee an optimistic
1998 except for the economy, according to a Gallup poll taken at
the end of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The survey shows 45 percent of Italians expect to see a better
1998 on the whole while 21 percent expect things to get worse.
</P>
<P>
The 24-point difference between optimists and pessimists was
the greatest in two years, compared to 19 points last year and 23
points in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Only 19 percent of the pollees expect an improvement in the
economy in the new year while 47 percent think the economy will
remain unimproved and 29 percent anticipate the situation to turn
more difficult.
</P>
<P>
Half of Italians expect unemployment to grow and only 19
percent of them expect a decline in the jobless rate. 
</P>
