<HEADLINE> Pakistan Radio to Counter Western Propaganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Radio Pakistan has planned a
special series of programs for broadcast from January to March to
counter western propaganda against Pakistan on child labor.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the series is to counter the concerted campaign
launched by western media targeting Pakistan on human rights
issues, official Associated Press of Pakistan reported on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The program, titled Respect for Humanity, is also expected to
dispel the impression of alleged widespread abuses of human rights
in Pakistan, APP said.
</P>
<P>
The weekly series, consisting of 13 programs will be put on the
air every Monday at 4.30 p.m. during the period, APP said.
