<HEADLINE> China's Top Consultative Body Holds New Year's Tea Party (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- The National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Council (CPPCC) held a tea
party here today to mark the coming of the new year.
</P>
<P>
Top Chinese leaders including Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao Shi,
Zhu Rongji, Li Ruihuan, Liu Huaqing, Wei Jianxing, Li Lanqing and
Rong Yiren attended the celebration.
</P>
<P>
Also present were leading members of the CPPCC National
Committee, non-Communist Parties, the All-China Federation of
Industry and Commerce (ACFIC), personalities without party
affiliation, seniors officials of departments of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the
government, and representatives of different circles and all
ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the tea party, President Jiang Zemin, who is general
secretary of the CPC Central Committee and chairman of the Central
Military Commission, extended festival greetings, on behalf of the
CPC Central Committee, the State Council and the Central Military
Commission, to all non-Communist parties, the ACFIC, non-Party
personages, to the broad masses of workers, farmers, intellectuals
and carders, to officers and men of the Chinese People's
Liberation Army (PLA), the armed police and public security
officers, to compatriots in the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region, Macao and Taiwan and overseas Chinese, and to people of
other countries who have shown concern or help for China's
modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Jiang called 1997 "a very important and extremely unusual year
in the history of our Party and nation."
</P>
<P>
After the death of Deng Xiaoping at the beginning of the year,
the whole Party, the whole army and people of all ethnic groups in
China rallied closely around the CPC Central Committee and
unswervingly adhered to the Party's basic theory and basic line to
push ahead the cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Government smoothly resumed the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong and maintained its prosperity and
stability, marking a stride forward in completing the
reunification of the motherland, he said.
</P>
<P>
The CPC's 15th National Congress held high the great banner of
Deng Xiaoping Theory, summed up historical experience, worked out
the Party's fundamental program in the primary stage of socialism
and unveiled a cross-century plan for reform, opening and
modernization.
</P>
<P>
Those two major political events greatly inspired the whole
Party and people of all ethnic groups in China in uniting more
closely and working hard to build China into a prosperous,
democratic and modernized country and to realize the reunification
of the motherland. More
nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
