<HEADLINE> China's Top Consultative Body Holds New Year's Tea Party (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In 1997, China also made notable headways in pushing forward
its reform, opening-up and modernization drive, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
The national economy continued its good growth momentum by
realizing high growth coupled with low inflation, with all major
economic indices basically reaching the macro-control targets,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
