<HEADLINE> Russia Beats Canada to Enter Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Russia edged defending
champion Canada 2-1 in overtime at the quarter-finals and gained
their top-four slot at the World Junior Ice Hockey Championship
here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Russia's Maksim Afinogenov scored the winning goal with 39
seconds left in overtime at Hameenlinna, Finland, to force the
exit of Canada, which had won the crown for five consecutive times.
</P>
<P>
Russia netted at 18:01 in the first period when Dimitri
Vlasenkov cut in from the side and managed to put the puck past
Canada's goalkeeper.
</P>
<P>
Canada came back to equalize through Daniel Tkaczuk at 2:31 to
extend the game into overtime.
</P>
<P>
The Czech Republic also sailed into the semi-finals by beating
the United States 4-1.
</P>
<P>
The Americans, which finished runner-up at last championship,
managed to score only the consolation goal through Brian Gionta at
11:24 in the last period.
</P>
<P>
The Czechs led the first period 1-0 and added two more in the
second period.
</P>
<P>
In other quarterfinals, Switzerland ousted Sweden in penalty
shooting after drawing 1-1 after the overtime, while Finland
scored a lopsided 14-1 victory over Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
In the semifinals Friday, Finland will meet Switzerland while
Russia plays the Czech Republic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
