<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Kenyan Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 1 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Kenyan newspapers today.
</P>
<P>
Kenya Times
</P>
<P>
-- Kenyan Electoral Commission Chairman Samuel Kivuitu held
his first press conference Wednesday after two days of silence
and conceded massive irregularities in the elections, but ruled
out resignation.
</P>
<P>
Daily Nation
</P>
<P>
-- Early returns from 61 constituencies at 10:30 last night
gave incumbent President Daniel arap Moi a comfortable lead over
his four leading challengers for the next five-year term of
presidency.
</P>
<P>
-- The overwhelming majority of Zimbabwean white farmers whose
land has been earmarked for compulsory purchase by the state have
appealed against the move, a government official said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
East African Standard
</P>
<P>
-- Moi was leading the field Wednesday with over 10 percent of
the votes counted in controversial and chaotic elections. While
Kenya's two main opposition leaders said they would reject an
elections victory by Moi. 
</P>
