<HEADLINE> Jiang: 1997 Diplomatic Work Scores Important Results </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- China's diplomatic work scored
important achievements in 1997, Chinese President Jiang Zemin said
here today.
</P>
<P>
At a new year tea party sponsored by the National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, Jiang said
that in the past year, China's good-neighborly relations with its
neighboring countries have been further strengthened.
</P>
<P>
China's unity and cooperation with the vast number of
developing nations have been further consolidated, and its ties
with the developed nations in the west have been improved and
enhanced, noted Jiang, also general secretary of the Chinese
Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
Through high-level exchanges of visits, Jiang said, China has
formulated goals and policies guiding its 21st-century-oriented
relations with such big nations as the United States, Russia,
France and Japan.
</P>
<P>
As of today, China normalized its ties and forged diplomatic
relations with South Africa, he said.
</P>
<P>
Also, the country has taken an active part in regional and
inter-continental economic, trade and technological cooperation
and exchanges, he said.
</P>
<P>
The president said that China's international status and its
influence in the world are being further enhanced, and the world's
media generally holds that the country is playing an increasingly
significant role in promoting world and regional peace, stability
and development.
</P>
<P>
In less than two decades of reform and opening-up, he
continued, "We have made achievements that has caught world-wide
attention and has laid a solid basis for new victories of our
cause," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
However, he warned that "we must see clearly that as
international competition is getting increasingly fierce, there
remains a long way to go in accomplishing the arduous task of
modernization in a country with a huge population of 1.2 billion."
</P>
<P>
The president reiterated that China will stick to its
independent foreign policy of peace, and continue to develop
friendly cooperative ties with all countries based on the five
principles of peaceful co-existence.
</P>
<P>
Together with people of the whole world, China will continue to
make positive contributions to the establishment of a fair and
reasonable new international order, to the lofty cause of
promoting the world peace and development, and to the opening-up
of a beautiful future for mankind, Jiang said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
