<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Cabinet Expanded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina has expanded her cabinet to include 37 ministers by the
induction of six new faces, the official news agency BSS reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
President Shahabuddin Ahmed administered the oath of office to
three ministers, four state ministers and a deputy minister on
Wednesday evening at a simple ceremony, presided over by Cabinet
Secretary Ataul Huq.
</P>
<P>
M.A. Mannan, former state minister in charge of labor and
manpower, was promoted to full minister, and Jinnatunnesa
Takukdar, former deputy minister for primary and mass education,
was elevated as state minister.
</P>
<P>
Mohiuddin Khan Alamghir, who was the state minister for
planning, civil aviation and tourism, has been given the charge of
the ministries of planning and science and technology, and
Dhirendra Devnath Shabhu, foreign deputy minister for shipping,
has been given the charge of the Ministry of Food.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time that Hasina expands her cabinet since
she came into office in June 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
