<HEADLINE> 9 Hurt in New Year's Revelry in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Preliminary reports showed that
at least nine people have been hurt by stray bullets fired by
those who violated government orders in New Year's revelry in the
Philippines, the Philippine News Agency reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The report said hospitals in Metro Manila alone reported that
they have initially admitted at least 95 persons victimized by
exploding firecrackers and more were still intermittently checking
in.
</P>
<P>
It added that the bulk of the patients poured in right after
the revelry reached its height at midnight. Streets in Manila were
reduced to nearly zero visibility at midnight due to the heavy
smoke brought about by exploding firecrackers.
</P>
<P>
However, Health Secretary Carmencita Reodica said the number of
blast victims were lower than that of last year. She added that a
final report on blast victims might be available latter Thursday.
</P>
<P>
During the celebration of New Year, several fires also took
place in Metro Manila and its nearby cities, destroying millions
of pesos worth of properties and injuring at least 20 people, the
report said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
