She said that independence is much more than throwing off the
shackles of foreign rule. It is the building of a new inclusive
political structure that will transcend divisive politics.
</P>
<P>
She added: "As committed democrats we must face all the
challenges, placing our trust in the wisdom and strength of the
people."
</P>
<P>
She called on the people to build a truly independent nation
putting behind the sufferings and divisions of the past.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Sirimavo Bandaranaike in her message to the
nation called on the people to work in unity with understanding,
determination and dedication.
</P>
<P>
She said the fervent wish of all Sri Lankans should be to
overcome the present calamities and transform Sri Lanka into a
country where all could live and work in unity and brotherhood.
</P>
