<HEADLINE> Thai Foreign Minister to Visit Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Thai Foreign Minister Surin
Pitsuwan will seek Singapore's cooperation in technology transfer
in telecommunications and industrial knowhow during his January
6-8 visit to Singapore, the Bangkok Post reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Surin will also propose developing Thailand as a manufacturing
base and market for Singapore-funded ventures as part of
cooperation in trade and investment.
</P>
<P>
The Thai minister's visit comes under the Thai-Singapore civil
service exchange program.
</P>
