<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Largest Bulk Shipping Firm Set Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 1 (Xinhua) -- The Bulk Shipping Company of the
China Ocean Shipping Group (COSCO), the largest bulk goods
shipping firm in the country, was founded in north China's Tianjin
Municipality today.
</P>
<P>
COSCO, the country's leading shipping company, has made it part
of its strategic efforts to reorganize its fleet to improve
management and efficiency.
</P>
<P>
According to its reform plan, COSCO branches will
specialize: Tianjin in bulk goods, Shanghai in containers, Dalian
in oil and Guangzhou in sundry goods.
</P>
<P>
The new-born COSCO Bulk Shipping Company has been based in
COSCO Tianjin, while the name of COSCO Tianjin will remain as well.
</P>
<P>
General Manager Wei Jiafu told Xinhua recently that the company
has more than 100 bulk cargo vessels with a tonnage of more than
two million tons and a staff of 11,000.
</P>
<P>
Wei, captain of ocean-going ships for 16 years, had led several
other big shipping companies and took the present post two years
ago. He said that local shipping firms have to adopt modern
managerial methods and make decisions in a scientific manner to
compete on the international market.
</P>
<P>
According to Wei, a Decision-Making Support System jointly
developed by his company and the Dalian Maritime University will
also be put into use as of today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
