<HEADLINE> Men's Giant Slalom in Austria Rescheduled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- A men's World Cup Alpine skiing
giant slalom, previously scheduled to be held in the Austrian town
of Hinterstoder on January 6, has been moved to another venue,
organizers said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The date of the race remained unchanged but it would be staged
in either of the Austrian resorts of Flachau and Schladming.
</P>
<P>
