the artificial snow at night.
</P>
<P>
Two men's super-giant slaloms and a night slalom to be held in
Schladming on January 8, 10 and 11 would go ahead as planned, they
added.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Tuesday, the International Skiing Federation moved
two women's races scheduled for Ofterschwang, Germany, between
January 5 and 6 to Bormio in Italy because of a lack of snow.
</P>
<P>
A men's downhill, postponed first at Val d'Isere and then at
Val Gardena, has been rescheduled for the Swiss resort of Wengen
on January 16. 
